Perfect! My test file was created successfully. Let me now summarize the changes I made:

## Summary

I've successfully fixed the issue where the prepublish modal was showing categories for pages when it shouldn't.

### Root Cause
In the `PrepublishingHomeViewModel.kt` file, the categories section was being added to both posts and pages unconditionally in the `setupHomeUiState` method. This caused pages to display the categories selection option, which is incorrect behavior.

### The Fix
Added a conditional check around the categories section to only add it for posts (when `!editPostRepository.isPage`):

```kotlin
// Only add categories for posts, not pages
if (!editPostRepository.isPage) {
    val categoriesString = getCategoriesUseCase.getPostCategoriesString(
        editPostRepository,
        site
    )

    add(HomeUiState(
        navigationAction = PrepublishingScreenNavigation.Categories,
        actionResult = if (categoriesString.isNotEmpty()) {
            UiStringText(categoriesString)
        } else {
            run { UiStringRes(R.string.prepublishing_nudges_home_categories_not_set) }
        },
        actionClickable = true,
        onNavigationActionClicked = ::onActionClicked
    ))
}
```

### Expected Behavior After Fix
- **For Posts**: Header, Publish, Tags, Categories, SocialHidden, Button (3 HomeUiState items)
- **For Pages**: Header, Publish, SocialHidden, Button (1 HomeUiState item - no tags or categories)

This ensures that when publishing a page, users will no longer see the prepublish modal asking them to select categories, which matches the expected behavior described in the issue.

The fix is minimal, targeted, and addresses the issue without breaking existing functionality. Pages and posts now have distinct prepublishing experiences as intended.

